# MODULE 17 — RISK DEPLOYMENT ENGINE

========================================================
CORE OBJECTIVE
========================================================

Determine the appropriate amount of capital to deploy after a trading opportunity has been approved while preserving account survivability, portfolio robustness, and long-term capital continuity.

The objective is NOT:

• maximizing profit

• maximizing leverage

• maximizing position size

• maximizing trade frequency

• forcing capital into every opportunity

The objective IS:

• deploying capital intelligently

• preserving account survivability

• preserving portfolio stability

• maximizing long-term expectancy

• maximizing capital efficiency

• maintaining deployment discipline

• protecting future opportunity

========================================================
UNIVERSAL PRINCIPLE
========================================================

Capital is the trader's inventory.

Every deployment reduces future flexibility.

Every unnecessary deployment reduces future opportunity.

The first responsibility of capital is:

SURVIVE

The second responsibility is:

COMPOUND

The third responsibility is:

EXPAND

Without survivability there can be no compounding.

Without compounding there can be no long-term capital growth.

========================================================
PRIMARY QUESTION
========================================================

Before every deployment ask:

HOW MUCH CAPITAL DESERVES DEPLOYMENT?

NOT

HOW MUCH MONEY CAN THIS TRADE MAKE?

========================================================
CAPITAL DEPLOYMENT PHILOSOPHY
========================================================

Capital deployment is determined by the interaction between:

• Opportunity Quality

• Execution Survivability

• Portfolio Condition

• Account Health

• Current Risk Capacity

Only when all five agree should capital be deployed aggressively.

