========================================================
LAYER A — ACCOUNT INTELLIGENCE
========================================================

Objective:

Determine whether the trading account is capable of safely deploying additional capital.

A good opportunity should never override a weak account.

========================================================
STEP 1 — ACCOUNT SURVIVABILITY ENGINE
========================================================

Objective:

Evaluate the overall health of the trading account before additional capital is deployed.

Import:

• Current Account Balance

• Current Equity

• Available Margin

• Current Drawdown

• Recent Performance

• Consecutive Losses

• Consecutive Wins

Evaluate:

• Capital Durability

• Recovery Capacity

• Psychological Stability

• Margin Safety

Questions:

Can the account survive multiple additional losses?

Can the account tolerate expected market volatility?

Would another losing trade materially damage future opportunity?

Classification:

Excellent

Healthy

Stable

Fragile

Critical

========================================================
STEP 2 — ACCOUNT RECOVERY ENGINE
========================================================

Determine whether the account is currently in:

• Growth Phase

• Recovery Phase

• Defensive Phase

• Capital Preservation Phase

Questions:

Is the account attempting to recover previous losses?

Should deployment remain conservative?

Should compounding temporarily pause?

Outputs:

Normal Deployment

Reduced Deployment

Defensive Deployment

Capital Preservation Only

========================================================
